{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Require all social media platforms to verify identity of accounts",
        "additional_details": "This could protect people against online hate and act as a deterrent to social media users writing hate online. Even with a nickname as a username, verification could mean a person can be traced and held responsible and deter people from writing hate and setting up fake accounts.\r\nThese extra layers of identification could also enable simpler identification of users, allowing action to be taken by platforms and authorities to deal with online hate.\r\nWe think this will create a safer online space for all.",
        "background": "Make identity verification a legal requirement for all existing and new users on social media platforms. Nicknames could be used to maintain anonymity in the public eye, but accounts will be linked to real identities to help ensure social media users can be traced by authorities.",
